# Product Spec: Historical Figures Advisory Board Feature for PersonaNexus\
\
## Overview\
PersonaNexus is an open-source tool for building AI agent personalities using business frameworks and archetypes.  \
This feature adds a **"Historical Figures Advisory Board"** pack \'97 a set of 10 pre-configured, optional personas inspired by public-domain historical figures.  \
Users can enable this pack to instantly create a virtual advisory board for strategic advice, decision-making, or simulations.\
\
**Goal**:  \
Enhance project growth by providing out-of-the-box value for modern business leaders. Allow mixing historical wisdom with existing frameworks (OCEAN, DISC, Jungian/16-Type, OKR, RACI, SWOT, etc.) to create richer, more insightful agents.\
\
**Scope**:  \
- New optional YAML pack with exactly 10 historical personas  \
- Integration with existing board/advisory features (if already built) or as standalone personas  \
- No breaking changes to core system \'97 added as an examples/pack folder  \
- Fully opt-in, user-customizable, with strong legal/ethical disclaimers\
\
**Target Release**: v1.5.0 (next minor version)\
\
## Key Requirements\
1. **Public Domain Safety**  \
   All figures must have died long enough ago that their core ideas, writings, and general personas are public domain.  \
   Use only "inspired by" phrasing. Include prominent disclaimer in UI, docs, and code.\
\
2. **Opt-In Toggle**  \
   Default: disabled (`enabled: false`).  \
   Users enable via YAML flag or CLI argument (`--historical-enabled`).\
\
3. **Integration with Existing Frameworks**  \
   - Link each figure\'92s traits to OCEAN (scores 1\'9610), DISC (primary style), and Jungian/MBTI-inspired type  \
   - Allow seamless mixing with business frameworks (e.g., Sun Tzu + SWOT for competitive strategy)  \
   - Support multi-agent "board meetings" (export as CrewAI crew, LangGraph graph, etc.)\
\
4. **Customization**  \
   All fields editable by user (traits, scores, lenses, rules).  \
   No hard-coded values that cannot be overridden.\
\
5. **Export Compatibility**  \
   Works with existing targets: CrewAI, LangGraph, OpenClaw, plain prompts.\
\
6. **Disclaimer** (must appear whenever pack is enabled)  \
   > These are fictional interpretations inspired by public-domain historical figures.  \
   > They are not official representations, endorsements, or direct quotes from copyrighted modern works.  \
   > Use responsibly and adapt to your context.\
\
## User Stories\
- As a user, I can enable the historical pack and instantly get a "board" of 10 figures for advisory input.  \
- As a business leader, I can query the board (e.g., "Advise on Q2 strategy") and get responses flavored by each figure\'92s mindset.  \
- As a developer/contributor, I can fork and add new historical figures via PR.\
\
